---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { CLIENT_ROSTER } from '../consts';
---

<BaseLayout title="About">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 pt-20 pb-24">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1
      class="mt-6 font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] text-5xl md:text-7xl font-semibold tracking-[-0.02em] leading-[1.02]"
    >
      A specialized engineering firm —
      <span class="font-[family-name:var(--font-editorial)] italic font-normal text-[var(--color-accent)]">
        with receipts.
      </span>
    </h1>

    <div class="mt-14 grid grid-cols-3 gap-6 border-y border-[var(--color-border)] py-8">
      <div>
        <div class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] text-3xl font-semibold text-[var(--color-fg)]">40+</div>
        <div class="eyebrow mt-2">Engineers globally</div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] text-3xl font-semibold text-[var(--color-fg)]">5+</div>
        <div class="eyebrow mt-2">Years in business</div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] text-3xl font-semibold text-[var(--color-fg)]">15+</div>
        <div class="eyebrow mt-2">Years avg partner experience AI/ML</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 prose prose-invert prose-lg max-w-none">
      <p>
        Datashop is a specialized engineering firm. We ship production systems for teams that
        can't afford hand-wavy AI — AAA game publishers, Crypto infrastructure, regulated fintech,
        and healthcare.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)]">The two shapes of our work</h2>

      <p>
        We've found the engagements we're best at cluster into two shapes. One is
        <strong>org-wide AI transformation</strong>: working with executive teams to map where
        AI actually changes the business, what needs to happen across functions, and what
        operating model survives the change.
      </p>

      <p>
        The other is <strong>MVP to production scale</strong>: picking up an AI system that's
        working for a few users and building the evaluation, observability, cost, and reliability
        practices that let it handle real load without cracking. This is the phase most teams
        are surprised by, and most of what goes wrong happens here.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)]">Who's behind this</h2>
      <p>
        Our leadership combines deep institutional experience with modern agility. Partners
        include a former NVIDIA engineer (15+ years in AI/ML/Stats) and a former McKinsey
        consultant. The founding partner has 19 years in AI/ML/Stats, starting his career as
        a quantitative analyst at a hedge fund.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)]">Client roster</h2>
      <p>
        We've shipped production systems for <strong>{CLIENT_ROSTER.join(', ')}</strong>,
        alongside several venture-backed startups.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)]">How we work</h2>
      <p>
        We parachute in, look at the real problem, and leave you with something durable. That
        means: a team that understands the system after we've gone, documentation that doesn't
        lie, and measurement that tells you when things are drifting.
      </p>
      <p>
        We don't take every engagement. If the fit's wrong we'll say so — and refer you to
        someone better suited.
      </p>

      <p>
        Tell us what you're working on. <a href="/contact">Start a conversation →</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
